<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Alegra Board — Discussion · Churn</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.js"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles/base.css">
  <style>
    /* ── Churn-specific additions ───────────────────────────────── */
    .hero-stat {
      display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .hero-num {
      font-size: 48px; font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -1.6px; line-height: 1;
      color: var(--color-navy);
    }
    .hero-num.teal { color: var(--color-teal); }
    .hero-num.red  { color: var(--color-negative); }
    .hero-unit {
      font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--color-neutral); letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    }
    .hero-cap {
      font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.5; max-width: 320px;
    }
    .hero-cap strong { color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .hero-delta {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
      font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;
      background: #dcfce7; color: var(--color-positive);
      padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 99px;
    }

    .chart-wrap { position: relative; flex: 1; min-height: 0; width: 100%; }

    /* stacked KPI column */
    .kpi-stack { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
    .kpi-stack .kpi-item { padding-top: 14px; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .kpi-stack .kpi-item:first-child { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }
    .kpi-stack .k-label {
      font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.3px;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-neutral); margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    .kpi-stack .k-val {
      font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.8px;
      line-height: 1; color: var(--color-navy); margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .kpi-stack .k-val.teal { color: var(--color-teal); }
    .kpi-stack .k-val.red  { color: var(--color-negative); }
    .kpi-stack .k-val.sm   { font-size: 20px; }
    .kpi-stack .k-note {
      font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.45;
    }
    .kpi-stack .k-note strong { color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600; }

    /* horizontal bars */
    .hbar-set { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; }
    .hbar-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr 48px;
      align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    }
    .hbar-name { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-weight: 500; }
    .hbar-track { height: 8px; background: #f1f5f9; border-radius: 2px; overflow: hidden; }
    .hbar-fill { height: 100%; background: var(--color-navy); border-radius: 2px; }
    .hbar-fill.teal { background: var(--color-teal); }
    .hbar-fill.red  { background: var(--color-negative); }
    .hbar-fill.gray { background: #94a3b8; }
    .hbar-val {
      font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-navy);
      text-align: right; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    }
    .hbar-row.em .hbar-name { color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .hbar-row.em .hbar-val  { color: var(--color-negative); }

    /* section-divider slide variant used for cover */
    .section-divider {
      background: var(--color-navy);
      justify-content: center;
      padding: var(--slide-pad-y) var(--slide-pad-x);
    }
    .section-divider .eyebrow {
      font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-teal);
      letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    .section-divider .section-title {
      font-size: 38px; font-weight: 700; color: #ffffff;
      letter-spacing: -1.2px; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 14px; max-width: 640px;
    }
    .section-divider .topic-label {
      font-size: 15px; font-weight: 400; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.40);
    }
    .section-divider .slide-num {
      position: absolute; bottom: 24px; right: var(--slide-pad-x);
      font-size: 10px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
    }

    /* ── Segmentation slides — prefix .dx- (diagnosis) and .sg- (proposal) ── */
    .dx-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 28px; height: 100%; }
    .dx-section-label { font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-teal); letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 12px; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; }
    .dx-challenge { display: flex; gap: 12px; padding: 11px 14px; background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 7px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-negative); }
    .dx-challenge .num { flex-shrink: 0; width: 26px; height: 26px; background: var(--color-negative); color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; margin-top: 1px; }
    .dx-challenge h3 { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 3px; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; }
    .dx-challenge p  { font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; }
    .dx-stats-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
    .dx-stat-card { background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px 18px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 18px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); flex: 1; }
    .dx-big-num { font-size: 34px; font-weight: 700; font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; letter-spacing: -1px; }
    .dx-big-num.negative    { color: var(--color-negative); }
    .dx-big-num.neutral-num { color: #d97706; }
    .dx-big-num.red         { color: #dc2626; }
    .dx-stat-label { font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; }
    .dx-stat-label strong { color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .sg-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; gap: 0; }
    .sg-image-wrap { border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 12px; flex-shrink: 0; height: 168px; }
    .sg-image-wrap img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: top; display: block; }
    .sg-changes-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 8px; flex: 1; }
    .sg-change-card { padding: 11px 12px; background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: 6px; border-top: 3px solid transparent; display: flex; flex-direction: column; overflow: hidden; }
    .sg-change-card.sg-amber { border-top-color: #d97706; }
    .sg-change-card.sg-blue  { border-top-color: #2563eb; }
    .sg-change-card.sg-teal  { border-top-color: var(--color-teal); }
    .sg-change-card.sg-core  { border-top-color: var(--color-core, #534AB7); }
    .sg-cc-tag { font-size: 8px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 6px; font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .sg-amber .sg-cc-tag { color: #d97706; }
    .sg-blue  .sg-cc-tag { color: #2563eb; }
    .sg-teal  .sg-cc-tag { color: var(--color-teal); }
    .sg-core  .sg-cc-tag { color: #534AB7; }
    .sg-change-card p { font-size: 10px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.48; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; overflow: hidden; }
    .sg-change-card p strong { color: var(--color-text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- ================================================================
       COVER — Discussion Topic Title
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide section-divider">
    <div class="eyebrow">Discussion · 01</div>
    <div class="section-title">Churn</div>
    <div class="topic-label">GLO + CORE Segment &nbsp;·&nbsp; Q1 2026</div>
    <div class="slide-num">1</div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 1 — ALEGRA GLOBAL CHURN · all segments
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
      <span class="title">Alegra at 4.8% monthly churn in Q1'26 (2025 baseline 4.65%) · Core at 3.5% remains the stability anchor, Lite ~2× higher</span>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-body" style="gap: 18px;">

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr; gap: 36px; flex: 1; min-height: 0;">

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 0;">
          <div class="block-label">Monthly Alegra total churn</div>
          <div class="chart-wrap"><canvas id="globalChart"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Q1'26 · at a glance</div>
          <div class="kpi-stack">
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Churn · (Retired − Reactivated) / BoP · monthly avg</div>
              <div class="k-val teal">4.8%</div>
              <div class="k-note">Q1'26 · 2025 baseline <strong>4.65%</strong> · trend: 5.08 → 5.27 → 4.03 (Mar strong recovery)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Companies flow · Q1'26 total</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">8,164<span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--color-neutral); font-weight:500;">&nbsp;net</span></div>
              <div class="k-note">12,408 retired − 4,244 reactivated · <strong>~28% of Q1 churn is Core</strong></div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">MRR flow · Q1'26 total</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">$268K<span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--color-neutral); font-weight:500;">&nbsp;net Q1</span></div>
              <div class="k-note">$384K retired − $116K reactivated · ~$89K/mo avg</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="insight-box">
        <span class="so-what">So what</span>
        Alegra-wide Q1'26 churn runs slightly above 2025 baseline (4.8% vs 4.65%) but March returned to 4.03% — sharp recovery. <strong>Core is where the defense matters most</strong> — only 28% of Q1 churn but ~39% of the active base. Next: zoom into Core's monthly flow and its real permanent impact.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-footer">
      <span class="footer-brand">Alegra · Confidential</span>
      <span class="footer-page">2</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 2 — CORE CHURN
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
      <span class="title">Core churn at 3.5% monthly avg in Q1'26 · 54 bps above 2025 baseline (2.93%) but March improved to 2.85%</span>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-body" style="gap: 18px;">

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr; gap: 36px; flex: 1; min-height: 0;">

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 0;">
          <div class="block-label">Monthly Core churn</div>
          <div class="chart-wrap"><canvas id="netChart"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Q1'26 · at a glance</div>
          <div class="kpi-stack">
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Churn · (Retired − Reactivated) / BoP · monthly avg</div>
              <div class="k-val teal">3.5%</div>
              <div class="k-note">Q1'26 · 2025 baseline <strong>2.93%</strong> · trend: 3.75 → 3.80 → 2.85 (Mar below baseline)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Companies flow · Q1'26 total</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">2,315<span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--color-neutral); font-weight:500;">&nbsp;net</span></div>
              <div class="k-note">3,479 retired − 1,164 reactivated · BoP avg 22,277</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">MRR flow · Q1'26 total</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">$124K<span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--color-neutral); font-weight:500;">&nbsp;net Q1</span></div>
              <div class="k-note">$176K retired − $51K reactivated · ~$41K/mo avg · ~$0.5M ARR/yr if sustained</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="insight-box">
        <span class="so-what">So what</span>
        Core Q1'26 ran 54 bps above the 2025 baseline (3.5% vs 2.93%) but <strong>March at 2.85% is already below baseline — recovery confirmed</strong>. Q1 net flow: <strong>2,315 companies and $124K MRR lost</strong>. Next: how many of these come back, and how many are permanent?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-footer">
      <span class="footer-brand">Alegra · Confidential</span>
      <span class="footer-page">3</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 3 — FULL FUNNEL · Gross → Permanent
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
      <span class="title">Full funnel · Core 2025 closed year: 4.20% gross → 2.39% permanent · 43% of retired companies come back within 3 months</span>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-body" style="gap: 18px;">

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr; gap: 36px; flex: 1; min-height: 0;">

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 0;">
          <div class="block-label">Core · Gross retirements vs Permanent</div>
          <div class="chart-wrap"><canvas id="grossChart"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Retention funnel · 2025 Core (closed window)</div>
          <div class="hbar-set">
            <div class="hbar-row" style="grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr 108px;">
              <div class="hbar-name">Gross retired</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill" style="width:100%; background:var(--color-navy);"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val">9,849 · 4.20%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row" style="grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr 108px;">
              <div class="hbar-name" style="color:var(--color-positive);">(−) Reactivated (+1 mo)</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill" style="width:31%; background:#86efac;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val" style="color:var(--color-positive);">3,015 · 1.29 pp</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row" style="grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr 108px;">
              <div class="hbar-name" style="color:var(--color-positive);">(−) Recovered (+2/+3 mo)</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill" style="width:12%; background:#86efac;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val" style="color:var(--color-positive);">1,222 · 0.52 pp</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row em" style="grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr 108px;">
              <div class="hbar-name" style="color:var(--color-teal);">= Permanent</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill teal" style="width:57%;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val" style="color:var(--color-teal);">5,612 · 2.39%</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top: 14px; font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.55;">
            Of every 100 retired in 2025: <strong style="color:var(--color-text-primary);">31 return at month +1</strong> · 12 at months +2/+3 · <strong style="color:var(--color-text-primary);">57 stay permanent</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="insight-box">
        <span class="so-what">So what</span>
        In the closed 2025 year, <strong>43% of Core retirements returned within 3 months</strong> — the permanent slice is ~57% of gross, the real LTV compression. Next: what <em>type</em> of churn composes this permanent loss — payments or voluntary?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-footer">
      <span class="footer-brand">Alegra · Confidential</span>
      <span class="footer-page">4</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 4 — CHURN MIX · voluntary vs involuntary
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
      <span class="title">Two-thirds of Core exits are a payments issue that auto-resolves — voluntary is smaller but permanent</span>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-body" style="gap: 20px;">

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.55fr 1fr; gap: 36px; flex: 1; min-height: 0;">

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 0;">
          <div class="block-label">Core churn · companies per month · voluntary vs involuntary</div>
          <div class="chart-wrap"><canvas id="volInvolChart"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Core mix · Q1'26</div>
          <div class="kpi-stack">
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Involuntary (delinquent)</div>
              <div class="k-val">63%</div>
              <div class="k-note">Payment failure · 47% auto-recovers</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Voluntary</div>
              <div class="k-val sm red">37%</div>
              <div class="k-note">Active cancel · strategic focus</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Core vs Lite · benchmark</div>
              <div class="k-val sm teal">~2×</div>
              <div class="k-note">2025 baseline: Lite 5.8% vs Core 2.93% · structural quality gap</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="insight-box">
        <span class="so-what">So what</span>
        Within Core, management focus belongs on the <strong>37% voluntary</strong> — smaller in volume but permanent in impact. Lite runs ~2× Core's rate on 2025 baseline, confirming Core as the stability moat. Next: who are these voluntary leavers, and when do they signal?
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-footer">
      <span class="footer-brand">Alegra · Confidential</span>
      <span class="footer-page">5</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 5 — WHO LEAVES · tenure + pre-exit behavior
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
      <span class="title">The typical Core leaver is a year-two+ veteran with falling usage and invoices — visible 90 days before exit</span>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-body" style="gap: 16px;">

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 44px; flex: 1; min-height: 0; align-items: start;">

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Core churn · share by tenure</div>
          <div class="hbar-set">
            <div class="hbar-row">
              <div class="hbar-name">M1 – M3</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill gray" style="width:16.0%;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val">16.0%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row">
              <div class="hbar-name">M4 – M6</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill gray" style="width:14.5%;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val">14.5%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row">
              <div class="hbar-name">M7 – M12</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill gray" style="width:16.3%;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val">16.3%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="hbar-row em">
              <div class="hbar-name">M13+</div>
              <div class="hbar-track"><div class="hbar-fill red" style="width:53.2%;"></div></div>
              <div class="hbar-val">53.2%</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.5;">
            Within M13+, <strong style="color:var(--color-text-primary);">monthly plans churn at 7.46% vs 2.02% annual</strong> — a 3.7× structural gap.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="block-label">Pre-exit behavior · what we observe</div>
          <div class="kpi-stack">
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Flagged on CHS at exit</div>
              <div class="k-val red">72%</div>
              <div class="k-note"><strong>Critical or At-risk</strong> · our score saw most before they left</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Product usage · final month</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">78%</div>
              <div class="k-note">had ≤5 transactions · low &amp; declining</div>
            </div>
            <div class="kpi-item">
              <div class="k-label">Invoice volume · 6 mo before exit</div>
              <div class="k-val sm">54 → 29<span style="font-size:13px; color:var(--color-neutral); font-weight:500;">&nbsp;/mo</span></div>
              <div class="k-note"><strong>−46%</strong> decline · voluntary Core churners · visible months before exit</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; gap: 18px; align-items: center; padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px;">
        <div style="font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.3px; color: var(--color-neutral); text-transform: uppercase; white-space: nowrap;">Top stated reasons · Q56</div>
        <div style="flex: 1; display: flex; gap: 20px; font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <span><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">"Sporadic use"</strong> &nbsp;35%</span>
          <span>"Other / no reason" &nbsp;36%</span>
          <span>"Switched provider" &nbsp;12%</span>
          <span>"Economic" &nbsp;10%</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-box">
        <span class="so-what">So what</span>
        The exit is <strong>detectable 90 days in advance</strong> — at-risk CHS, low usage, dropping invoices. And the customer's words align: 35% self-report "sporadic use". Next: the clearest behavioral signal — how invoice volume decays before exit.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="slide-footer">
      <span class="footer-brand">Alegra · Confidential</span>
      <span class="footer-page">6</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="slide-divider">↓</div>

  <!-- ================================================================
       SLIDE 6 — PRE-EXIT SIGNAL · invoice decline
       ================================================================ -->
  <div class="slide">
    <div class="slide-header">
